The paper proposes a variant of the Frank-Wolfe algorithm for solving sparse/low-rank optimization problems, which are common in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions classification tasks, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant sub-category. The proposed algorithm also reduces per-iteration cost, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
